{"PageNumber":25,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Mitigating DNS Cache Poisoning","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":308},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":187},"RightBottom":{"X":1898,"Y":308},"RightTop":{"X":1898,"Y":187}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● First, most DNS cache poisoning attacks are targeted towards ISP DNS servers, known as local DNS (LDNS) servers, rather than authoritative name servers","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":671},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":444},"RightBottom":{"X":2636,"Y":671},"RightTop":{"X":2636,"Y":444}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"• Prior to more recent cache poisoning attacks, the practice of leaving LDNS servers openly accessible to the outside world was common, but since 2008, most LDNS servers have been reconfigured to only accept requests from within their internal network","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1028},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":713},"RightBottom":{"X":2592,"Y":1028},"RightTop":{"X":2592,"Y":713}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● This prevents all cache poisoning attempts originating from outside of an ISP's network","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1212},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1062},"RightBottom":{"X":2650,"Y":1212},"RightTop":{"X":2650,"Y":1062}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● However, the possibility of attacking from within the network remains.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1334},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1254},"RightBottom":{"X":2650,"Y":1334},"RightTop":{"X":2650,"Y":1254}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● There are some other techniques not explored here, but the possibility of DNS Cache Poisoning still exists","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1527},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1368},"RightBottom":{"X":2325,"Y":1527},"RightTop":{"X":2325,"Y":1368}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}